The paper discusses a novel approach for training deep neural networks using Bayesian techniques, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on evaluating model uncertainty and overfitting, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for approximating the posterior distribution, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY).
